{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: source clients -> aggregator -> summary input payload (MOCK-MISS yes). No real OS/network/subprocess is required to reproduce the specific omission bug; in-process fakes for the three sources can expose missing/overwritten fields (REAL-INFRA no, MOCK-HIDE no). LLM output quality is not under test because assertion is on pre-generation input content (LLM-DEP no). MULTI-STEP no. Candidate check: Integration test wires real aggregator + three stub clients, asserts summary-generator receives payload containing all three sections; catches dropped-source mapping bug. Adjacent Unit test on only payload-builder function could miss wiring/config mismatch between collector modules; therefore Unit is too low. Rejected higher level (System) because behavior text is specifically about \"content passed to the summary-generation step,\" not real network/email/runtime effects.","test_description":"Run collector/aggregation modules together with three deterministic fake source adapters returning distinct markers. Invoke report build up to (and including) call boundary into summary generator, and assert call arguments include all three source datasets with correct section keys.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears in cross-module error propagation and fallback rendering (source adapter exception/timeout signal -> report assembler -> section note), so Unit is too low (MOCK-MISS yes). Real OS/network is not required for the stated behavior; a stubbed source that raises the same exception type is sufficient (REAL-INFRA no). Mocking does not inherently hide this failure because the fallback path is exactly what stubbed failure drives (MOCK-HIDE no). No dependence on model judgment quality (LLM-DEP no) and no multi-agentic chain (MULTI-STEP no). Candidate check: Integration test with one failing source adapter + two healthy adapters asserts report still generated and includes `data unavailable` for failed section; catches abort-on-first-error wiring bug. Adjacent Unit test for only formatter adding fallback text would miss orchestration bug where pipeline exits before formatter. Rejected higher level (System) because behavior text only requires graceful handling of \"one data source unavailable,\" not real network stack semantics.","test_description":"Wire report pipeline modules with fake adapters; configure one adapter to raise an availability error. Execute weekly report generation and assert process completes, failed section contains `data unavailable`, and other sections remain populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on summary content quality (faithfulness to key values), which is model judgment/output behavior if the summary step is LLM-based; deterministic stubs would always pass and hide hallucination/omission failures (LLM-DEP yes, deterministic-assertion trap applies). Single model-output evaluation step, not a chained multi-agent loop (MULTI-STEP no), so Workflow is unnecessary. Candidate check: Agentic test feeds known fixture data into real summarizer and asserts extracted claims in output match expected key values/tolerances; catches factual drift/hallucinated numbers. Adjacent Integration test with canned model response only verifies plumbing and cannot detect real misrepresentation. Rejected higher level (Workflow) because behavior text targets one summary step: \"The narrative summary accurately represents...\" with no multi-step agent pipeline.","test_description":"Use fixed input datasets with unambiguous key metrics and run the real summary-generation dependency. Evaluate output for factual consistency against source values (e.g., required key-value mentions and no contradictory numeric claims), with repeat runs/thresholds to account for nondeterminism.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Stated failure boundary includes real delivery to inbox, which depends on real HTTP/service/network and email infrastructure behavior (REAL-INFRA yes; MOCK-HIDE yes because mocked mail APIs can pass while SMTP/API auth, routing, or provider acceptance fails). This is end-to-end system validation, but not inherently dependent on LLM decision quality for pass/fail of inbox delivery (LLM-DEP not required by behavior text). MULTI-STEP agentic chain not required. Candidate check: System test runs full script against test endpoints and a real test mailbox, then asserts message arrival, recipient, subject/body structure. Adjacent Integration test with mocked mail client catches orchestration but misses provider/network/inbox acceptance failures. Rejected higher levels (Agentic/Workflow) because behavior text is \"reaches ... inbox correctly,\" not summary quality or multi-agent reasoning.","test_description":"Execute scheduled job (or equivalent invocation) in a staging environment with real source endpoints and real email delivery path to a test inbox. Assert one email is received by configured recipient with expected report payload and metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior crosses real infrastructure boundaries: unreachable delivery service condition plus durable local file persistence and next-run retry semantics (process/scheduler/filesystem interaction). In-process mocks can miss permission/path/atomic-write and run-to-run state issues (REAL-INFRA yes, MOCK-HIDE yes). No dependence on AI output quality (LLM-DEP no) and no multi-agentic sequence (MULTI-STEP no). Candidate check: System test induces real delivery endpoint failure, runs job, asserts fallback file written on disk; then restores delivery and triggers next scheduled run, asserting queued report is sent and fallback state cleared. Adjacent Integration test with mocked filesystem/scheduler may miss real persistence or scheduling boundary failures. Rejected higher levels (Agentic/Workflow) because behavior text concerns retry/persistence on delivery outage, not model decisions.","test_description":"In staging, force email service/network unreachable during run 1 and verify report is persisted to local fallback path. On run 2 (service restored), verify persisted report is retried/sent successfully and retry artifact is removed or marked delivered.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
